Level

The number of global STI capacity building initiatives according to the level of STI expertise required. The advanced level indicates that the course covers STI policy best practice, emerging issues, case studies, indicators of success and how to track impact, whilst targeting individuals with a high level of knowledge and expertise. The intermediate level covers the basics of STI policy and some prior knowledge of policymaking is desirable for participation. The basic level covers the very basics of policymaking and barriers to entry are very low as no prior knowledge and experience are required.

Topics by SDG Connection

SDG Connection

The number of global STI capacity building initiatives according to the strength of their connection to the SDGs. A high connection indicates that the training is highly relevant to the SDGs and is an explicit connection made in the course title or description. A medium connection suggests that sustainability may be a significant focus of the initiative, although there is no explicit connection made to the SDGs. A low connection shows that there is little to no mention of sustainability in the course.
